WEBVTT

00:01.186 --> 00:10.399
Father, it has been said so clearly already that what needs to happen in this room, a sermon, a human cannot make happen.

00:11.721 --> 00:13.563
Taste and see that the Lord is good.

00:14.324 --> 00:16.227
There is a spiritual taste.

00:16.708 --> 00:29.746
There are capacities for enjoyment in the soul that cannot be awakened any other way than by the miracle of your indwelling, empowering spirit.

00:30.786 --> 00:42.982
So we invite you to come in power and to do that kind of awakening of joy in Jesus that is greater than joy in anything else.

00:44.064 --> 00:45.786
I asked this in his name, amen.

00:47.188 --> 00:50.152
So the focus for the weekend is enjoying Jesus.

00:50.933 --> 01:00.786
And so I want to begin by making the case from the gospel of John that saving faith in Jesus.

01:00.898 --> 01:10.252
So as basic as it can be, saving faith in Jesus is the awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

01:13.297 --> 01:22.550
So I don't think the gospel of John or the New Testament teaches that the enjoyment of Jesus is stage two.

01:23.752 --> 01:30.322
So first you get saved, you believe, and then maybe

01:30.594 --> 01:36.163
Sometimes later you learn that there's such a thing as enjoying Jesus.

01:36.343 --> 01:49.043
I'm arguing that to be saved, to be converted, to be born again, to have saving faith is to experience an awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

01:50.545 --> 01:56.274
And that can be very threatening, very unsettling to you.

01:57.666 --> 02:06.376
because there are genuine believers among you who think that you don't enjoy Jesus.

02:07.177 --> 02:14.244
And you've been scratching your head since you heard of this church and saw that, it's written right here, enjoy Jesus' big disciples.

02:14.845 --> 02:20.992
You've been scratching your head like, is that how essential is that?

02:22.353 --> 02:26.418
And I've just said it's as essential as it can get.

02:27.586 --> 02:34.439
which is scary if you are saying to yourself right now in this room, but I think I'm saved.

02:37.124 --> 02:39.568
And I don't enjoy Jesus.

02:45.099 --> 02:51.250
A few weeks ago, I was in Washington, D.C., sat down at a dinner table.

02:51.362 --> 03:13.670
A man said to him beside me, who loves our ministry in the 60s, he had gone through a crisis of it two years earlier, and he just confessed to me, he said, message on, I hope in the Lord, I trust in the Lord, but ever since that crisis, I don't experience joy in Jesus.

03:16.894 --> 03:20.338
And here's a man who's been Christian for 50 years,

03:20.610 --> 03:25.117
And he's telling me that he doesn't enjoy Jesus.

03:26.620 --> 03:35.254
And so I responded to him the way I would respond to you if you came up to me after this service and said, I'm a Christian.

03:35.875 --> 03:36.957
I know I'm a Christian.

03:37.538 --> 03:40.743
I trust Jesus, but I don't enjoy Jesus.

03:42.386 --> 03:44.850
I said to him, I don't believe you.

03:48.322 --> 03:54.068
And over the next 15 or 20 minutes, I've said this to many people for 40 years, I've said this to people.

03:54.549 --> 03:56.951
I don't believe you.

03:56.971 --> 04:17.554
For the next 10, 20 minutes we had, we're talking about this very earnestly, I drew out of him significant expressions of glad affections for God, for the goodness of God, for the patience of God,

04:17.986 --> 04:33.468
for the power of God, for the preciousness of Christ, affections like thankfulness, like treasuring Christ, like hope in Christ.

04:34.450 --> 04:43.643
And I pointed out to him, and I'm pointing out to you now, that thankfulness is not a grim emotion.

04:44.745 --> 04:45.746
It's a glad emotion.

04:47.810 --> 04:48.311
It is.

04:50.353 --> 04:54.618
And treasuring Christ is not a gloomy emotion.

04:55.880 --> 04:56.981
It's a glad emotion.

04:57.422 --> 05:07.954
Even if it exists in the midst of sorrow and there are tears on your face as you are thankful and treasuring Jesus.

05:11.699 --> 05:16.044
Hope is not a dark, cheerless emotion.

05:16.404 --> 05:17.746
It's a glad emotion.

05:18.178 --> 05:26.549
even in prison, witness Paul, even in the hospital, even at the grave side.

05:27.690 --> 05:28.892
Hope is a glad emotion.

05:35.681 --> 05:45.714
In other words, I want to warn you here at the outset that some of you have conceptions of enjoying Jesus

05:46.818 --> 05:48.020
that are inadequate.

05:49.282 --> 05:58.656
You have conceptions, ideas in your head, of what it means to enjoy Jesus, that are inadequate to account for biblical reality.

05:59.778 --> 06:01.140
And I'm here to fix them.

06:04.425 --> 06:06.047
Do you have a conception?

06:06.087 --> 06:15.922
Indeed, do you have an experience of joy that can account for 2 Corinthians 6, 10, sorrowful

06:16.226 --> 06:30.915
yet always rejoicing, sorrowful, yet always, not after the sorrow in, under, through the sorrow, always rejoicing.

06:31.055 --> 06:32.097
You have a category for that.

06:32.418 --> 06:33.740
You have an experience of that.

06:34.302 --> 06:38.610
If you don't, you will not be able to make sense out of this church or the Bible.

06:42.402 --> 06:44.664
Do you have a category that makes sense?

06:44.684 --> 06:51.492
Do you have a conception of enjoying Jesus that makes sense out of 2 Corinthians 7, 4?

06:52.573 --> 06:55.836
Where Paul says, in all our afflictions.

06:55.876 --> 07:02.863
Now you've got to pause there and remember chapter 11, chapter 6, where he lists 26 horrors that he walks through.

07:03.264 --> 07:09.170
Paul lived a life of continual threat and sorrow and grief and pain

07:09.570 --> 07:15.379
in and out of prison, in and out of beatings, in and out of lacerations on his back, in and out of conflicts.

07:15.659 --> 07:20.106
He lived a life of continual weeping, I would dare say.

07:22.269 --> 07:27.317
And he says, in all our afflictions we are overflowing with joy.

07:27.377 --> 07:35.249
And you just want to say, Paul, do you have a conception of joy that can account for that?

07:35.269 --> 07:38.514
Do you have an experience of joy that would

07:38.754 --> 07:40.095
makes sense out of that.

07:40.356 --> 07:47.342
Or Ecclesiastes, I told the staff today, I was going to quote Ecclesiastes for the first time in defense of Christian hedonism.

07:47.362 --> 07:47.883
So here it is.

07:50.305 --> 08:03.357
Ecclesiastes 7, 3, sorrow is better than laughter because by sadness of faith, the heart is made glad.

08:03.417 --> 08:08.402
You just want to shake your head and say,

08:09.474 --> 08:11.537
What possibly could that be?

08:13.379 --> 08:17.625
By sorrow of faith, tears stained face.

08:21.750 --> 08:24.454
The heart is made glad.

08:25.856 --> 08:27.358
Here's my paraphrase.

08:29.982 --> 08:39.314
There are experiences of loss and grief in life that take you to depths

08:39.778 --> 08:44.824
of joy you could not have known any other way.

08:44.844 --> 08:46.886
If you're old enough, you know what I'm talking about.

08:47.667 --> 08:49.008
Brand new Christians, maybe not.

08:49.569 --> 08:54.855
But if you've walked with the Lord long enough, you know what He's talking about.

08:54.895 --> 09:08.370
There are dark nights, there are losses, there are griefs, there are struggles, there are sorrows where He shows up and He's tasted in that in a way He could not be tasted any other way.

09:10.306 --> 09:13.269
So I'm asking you, do you have categories in your head?

09:13.289 --> 09:20.977
Do you have conceptions and ideas about what the enjoyment of Jesus is so that you don't jump to the conclusion?

09:21.218 --> 09:24.021
I guess I'm not a Christian because I don't.

09:25.442 --> 09:26.103
Are you sure?

09:26.143 --> 09:31.849
So let me work on this with you in John, John's gospel for a bit.

09:32.450 --> 09:40.178
And I'm hoping that by the time we're done, the only people that think you're an unbeliever in this room would be unbelievers.

09:41.314 --> 09:42.636
And we really care about you.

09:43.056 --> 09:44.317
This church cares about you.

09:44.958 --> 09:45.939
And I care about you.

09:46.100 --> 09:47.041
And we're praying.

09:47.081 --> 09:54.990
We've prayed weeks before and in the room earlier today that you would know him and enjoy him before we're done.

09:56.912 --> 09:58.514
So all that by way of warning.

09:59.255 --> 10:09.106
I'm just warning you not to be too pessimistic about yourself as I lay out the argument that saving face

10:10.050 --> 10:13.594
is the awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

10:17.158 --> 10:39.762
One of the most provocative statements about saving faith is that the book in the Bible that talks most about coming to eternal life through saving faith, namely the Gospel of John,

10:41.378 --> 10:53.069
never uses the word faith in all 21 chapters and uses the word believe 98 times.

10:55.011 --> 11:00.476
The noun belief or faith does not occur in the Gospel of John.

11:01.878 --> 11:05.982
The verb believe occurs 98 times.

11:09.165 --> 11:10.706
That cannot be an accident.

11:13.314 --> 11:18.762
And I've spent a lot of time thinking, I want to understand, John, why you did it that way.

11:19.683 --> 11:21.706
What were you thinking?

11:23.048 --> 11:32.020
That must have taken some effort to use the word pistillo 98 times and never use the word pistis faith.

11:35.124 --> 11:39.671
So this message is an effort to explain why that is.

11:40.953 --> 11:42.034
And I make no

11:42.754 --> 11:46.417
pretense that I've got the whole thing figured out.

11:47.038 --> 11:55.706
Because the Gospel of John, probably more than any other book in the Bible, has layers of meaning.

11:57.148 --> 12:05.535
It is a mysteriously layered book, which is why you give it to brand new believers.

12:09.940 --> 12:12.562
And it's the deepest book there is, maybe.

12:13.730 --> 12:16.073
At least that's my experience of the Gospel of John.

12:16.113 --> 12:18.215
You take off, oh, I get that.

12:19.057 --> 12:23.562
For God's the love of the world, he gave his only son, whoever believes in him, and not perish, and have eternal life.

12:23.842 --> 12:24.603
Give that everywhere.

12:24.884 --> 12:27.206
Hang it over, ball-filled fences.

12:29.710 --> 12:39.642
And then you get this massive doctrine of predestination in chapter 10, and the election, and then he's...

12:39.662 --> 12:39.922
Okay.

12:40.066 --> 12:41.608
So that's the mystery for me.

12:42.169 --> 12:47.456
98 times the verb, zero times the noun, what's he up to?

12:49.479 --> 13:01.496
Sometimes scholars, pastors will say, okay, what he's up to is that he's trying to show that faith is active.

13:03.839 --> 13:05.181
